						<h2 class="question">
							What is a Bug Out Retreat?
						</h2>

						<p>
							A <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Retreat_%28survivalism%29">bug out retreat</a> is a place of refuge for those who in the preparedness/survival movement.  Often called a "Bug Out Location" or "BOL", they are a self sufficient, secluded, easily defended, homestead that would be used in troubled times to escape the chaos, violence, and other effects of possible threats and disasters.</p>
							<p>
								Within a tank of gas of your home, a secure bug out retreat maintains at the ready stores of food and water, clothes, medical and other supplies, off grid power, and more.  Ready for your arrival a moment's notice.</p>


