								<h4 class="black">The Typical Bug Out Location</h4>
								<p>Most survivalists cannot afford to live at a rural retreat year round.  They have jobs, families, etc.  Many choose to setup their retreat for an 11th hour departure, quietly arriving and sustaining themselves for the duration of the chaos.</p>
								<p>Such a retreat is time consuming to build, tremendously expensive, and burdensome to maintain.  Limited space and supplies eliminates the possibility of inviting even friends and family.  You're on your own, and so are they.  You end up loan wolfing it, hoping to avoid threats at your retreat because you know a few men cannot possibly maintain operations and security 24x7 for very long.</p>

								<h4 class="black">Our Bug Out Retreats</h4>
								<p>Mainstream Preppers is forming professionally designed, year round maintained, self sufficient and secure retreats for those who wish to team up with like minded people and be prepared as a team.</p>
